===Etymology===
From {{inh|zh|sit-pro|*m-k(r)əw||dove, pigeon}} ({{zh-ref|Benedict, 1974}}; {{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}; STEDT). Compare {{cog|bo|འང་གུ|འང་'''གུ'''|pigeon}}, {{cog|tbq-lol-pro|*m-krəw²}}, {{cog|my|ချိုး}}, {{cog|tbq-kuk-pro|*khruu}}.

In some southern Chinese dialects, {{l|zh|鳩||tr=--}} is pronounced with aspirated initial {{IPAchar-lite|/kʰ/}} due to taboo considerations.

